Citation.sAbstract: The article deals with measuring the densities of phenol, acetanilide, benzamide, benzoic acid, phenacetin,  i-(acetylamino)-benzoic acid, i-hydroxy-benzamide, and i-acetaminophen (where i = 1, 2, 3) in 1-octanol  in the wide concentration interval at T = 298.15 K. It also concerns the evaluation of apparent molar  volumes and partial molar volumes at infinite dilution, V0  2 as well as comparative analysis of the free volumes  per molecule in the octanolic solutions, Vfree  2 , and in the crystal lattices, Vfree  2 (cr), from the nature  and position of the substitutes. Also described is the evaluation of the increments of V0  2 and Vfree  2 for  the unsubstituted molecules and isomers and the methods to obtain partial molar volumes for various  functional groups at infinite dilution in 1-octanol at T = 298.15 K. Also considered is the limiting partial  molar volume of the solutes in terms of the scaled particle theory.
Citation.sTitle: Partial molar volumes of some drug and pro-drug substances in 1-octanol at T = 298.15 K
